This paper proposes an extension of the CRISP-DM process model for data mining, specifically addressing challenges related to context and model reuse handling. This topic is highly relevant to several sub-fields within computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information retrieval (cs.IR), and databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper discusses the need for software engineering practices to support context-aware data mining, which could also place it within the software engineering (cs.SE) category.
